FBIS4-1405 "drafr082_c_94019" FBIS-AFR-94-082 Daily Report 27 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA New National Flag Raised After Midnight 27 Apr New National Flag Raised After Midnight 27 Apr MB2704091694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 27 Apr 94 MB2704091694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] This morning people woke up to a new South Africa after the interim constitution came into effect at midnight. The new national flag was raised at ceremonies at a minute past midnight to the singing of the South African two national anthems, "Die Stem" ["The Voice"] and "Nkosi Sikelel' iAfrika" ["God Bless Africa"].
